The paper deals with the detection and localization of fingerprint alterations using CNN models and GANs. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of GANs for generating altered fingerprint images also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of a database of altered fingerprints, which can be considered as a multimedia dataset, placing it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
